{"event_id": "349c647f-c125-4feb-94cd-39bdd9ff32f1", "trace_id": "0222adad737b4c89", "session_id": "3147b617", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T13:09:12.952007+00:00", "tool": "filesystem.write_file", "args_hash": "608336adec8a80dca4261aae6b67c736bf78ea204402072dfde9b9888ec2ff3e", "args_redacted": {"path": "workspace/llm_frameworks.txt", "content": "Top 5 Open Source LLM Frameworks (2026)\n========================================\n\n1. LangChain - Python orchestration framework for building LLM-powered applications with chained prompts, memory, and tool integration.\n\n2. LlamaIndex - Data indexing and retrieval framework designed for connecting LLMs to external data sources and building RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) applications.\n\n3. Haystack - NLP pipeline framework by deepset for building search systems, question answering, and conversational AI with modular components.\n\n4. AutoGen - Multi-agent conversation framework by Microsoft that enables multiple AI agents to collaborate and solve complex tasks autonomously.\n\n5. CrewAI - Role-based agent framework for orchestrating collaborative AI teams where agents assume specific roles and work together on tasks.\n"}, "input_labels": {"SI": "SI:MED", "DS": "DS:NORMAL"}, "policy_decision": "ALLOW", "matched_rule": "", "rule_reason": "No matching rule; allowed", "prev_event_hash": "0b0b9060d70a7559f33d758a077df7f0a9f14623eff9b90f3e6e70d400df7b35", "event_hash": "a96c0c147cbe351d2d863fd2e0dfe2375617706773d9412e33d062d55fe67da9"}
